'''Miwa Shrine''' (三和神社) is a {{ill|Tochigi Prefecture|ja|栃木県|12=draft|12=draft}}{{ill|Nasu District|ja|那須郡|12=draft|12=draft}}{{ill|Nakagawa Town|ja|那珂川町|12=draft|12=draft}} Miwa-based {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft}}. It is a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|12=draft|12=draft}}, and its former shrine ranking according to the {{ill|Modern Shrine Ranking System|ja|近代社格制度|lt=Old Shrine Rank|lt_ja=旧社格|12=draft|12=draft}} was that of a {{ill|Gosha|ja|郷社|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref name="#1">『栃木県神社誌』，898頁</ref>.

== deity ==
* {{ill|Ōmononushi|ja|大物主|lt=Ōmononushi-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=大物主命|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref name="#1"/>

== History ==
According to the shrine legend, the shrine was founded in the 12th year of {{ill|Empress Suiko|ja|推古天皇|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|604|ja|604|12=draft|12=draft}}) after being enshrined from {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|大和国|12=draft|12=draft}} (present-day {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|12=draft|12=draft}}) {{ill|Ōmi Shrine|ja|大神神社|12=draft|12=draft}},<ref name="#1"/> and is identified with the Miwa Shrine of Nasu District in {{ill|Shimotsuke Province|ja|下野国|12=draft|12=draft}} as listed in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref>『栃木県神社誌』，41頁</ref>.

{{ill|Fujiwara no Sukeya|ja|藤原資家|lt=Sudo Gon-no-mori Sadamune|lt_ja=須藤権守貞信|12=draft|12=draft}} is said to have prayed for victory when suppressing bandits<ref>『栃木県の歴史散歩』，68頁</ref>. In the first year of {{ill|Tenyō|ja|天養|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|1144|ja|1144|12=draft|12=draft}}), he constructed the shrine’s buildings, and thereafter it was preserved by his descendants, the Nasu clan, until the clan was deposed<ref name="#1"/>. After their removal, the shrine has been maintained by its parishioners<ref name="#1"/>.

The Miwa Ten Festival held at this shrine was designated as a town-designated {{ill|Folk Cultural Property|ja|民俗文化財|lt=Intangible Folk Cultural Property|lt_ja=無形民俗文化財|12=draft|12=draft}} in the 6th year of {{ill|Heisei|ja|平成|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|1994|ja|1994|12=draft|12=draft}})<ref>{{Cite web|和書|author=那珂川町|url=https://www.town.tochigi-nakagawa.lg.jp/22kankou/category/jinjya/2009-1217-1720-52.html|title=町指定文化財（民俗文化財）|language=日本語|accessdate=2012-08-30|url-status=|url-status-date=}}</ref>.

